### Parse date-only strings as LOCAL
```js
// BAD — parses as UTC
new Date('2026-03-01')

// GOOD — parses as local
const [y, m, d] = '2026-03-01'.split('-').map(Number);
new Date(y, m - 1, d);
```

### Use the project's helper
```js
import { getLocalISODate, getLocalYearMonth } from '@/lib/local-date';
// These always use local timezone
```

